📋 Pain Point Analysis (4 Dimensions):

  A. Pain Points:
    1. Core messaging architecture cannot support Canvas App complexity - enabling 'interactive websites' and external publishing requires new infrastructure layer
    2. Multi-bot orchestration creating state management complexity - @-mention feature and response comparison require sophisticated coordination
    3. Team scaling faster than leadership capacity - new hires joining without sufficient senior guidance
    4. Technical debt accumulating from rapid feature velocity threatening long-term scalability
    5. Engineering-product alignment gaps causing inefficient prioritization and rework

  B. Strategic Needs:
    1. Build platform foundation to expand beyond chat into app hosting/publishing ecosystem
    2. Establish senior engineering layer to maintain quality during team expansion
    3. Maintain competitive feature velocity against OpenAI/Anthropic direct channels in AI arms race
    4. Create architectural patterns that scale with millions of users while enabling quick iteration

  C. Risks if Unfilled:
    1. Feature velocity collapses as Canvas App and multi-bot complexity overwhelms existing team
    2. New hires struggle without mentorship, increasing defect rates and onboarding time from months to 6+ months
    3. Technical debt blocks new AI model integrations, missing competitive launches by weeks or months
    4. Engineering-product misalignment wastes engineering cycles on deprioritized features

  D. Success Metrics:
    1. Canvas App infrastructure supports 1,000+ published apps within 6 months of hire
    2. Core messaging system scales to 10M+ daily active users without latency degradation
